---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SupportSection from "../components/SupportSection.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Moss - your home for every journey"
  description="Moss is a calm travel companion for planning trips, keeping places and notes together, and remembering every journey."
  ogTitle="Moss"
>
  <main>
    <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="kicker">A quiet home for travel</p>
        <h1 id="hero-title">Moss</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Plan what is ahead, hold onto what matters, and keep every trip
          connected in one thoughtful place.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a
            class="button button-moss"
            href="mailto:support@getmoss.app?subject=Moss%20TestFlight"
            >Request TestFlight access</a
          >
          <a class="button button-line" href="#journeys">Explore Moss</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="journey-panel" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="memory-card card-primary">
          <span>Kyoto</span>
          <strong>Spring days, temple walks, quiet dinners.</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="memory-card card-secondary">
          <span>Next</span>
          <strong>Notes, places, stays, and plans in one place.</strong>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="feature-band" id="journeys" aria-labelledby="journeys-title">
      <p class="kicker">Before / During / After</p>
      <h2 id="journeys-title">A place for the whole trip.</h2>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <article>
          <span>01</span>
          <h3>Plan with room to breathe</h3>
          <p>
            Keep dates, destinations, travel times, activities, meals, and notes
            together without turning the trip into a spreadsheet.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>02</span>
          <h3>Travel with context</h3>
          <p>
            Moss starts with itineraries and grows toward maps, stays,
            recommendations, companions, and the details you need nearby.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>03</span>
          <h3>Return to the memory</h3>
          <p>
            Every journey should stay useful after it ends, with favourite
            places, photos, notes, and journals ready to revisit.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="memory-section" id="memory" aria-labelledby="memory-title">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker">Built to grow</p>
        <h2 id="memory-title">More than an itinerary.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        Moss is beginning with planning because every trip needs a shape. The
        long-term home is broader: shared trips, restaurants, hotels, flights,
        packing, expenses, photos, journals, and the small details that make a
        place feel yours.
      </p>
    </section>

    <SupportSection />
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
